    <h4><span class="highlight">OPOWER Today</span></h4>
        
    <p>Our all-star team of software engineers, product specialists, behavioral scientists, statisticians, marketing experts, infographic designers, and efficiency advocates is about 175 people strong today, and we should reach 300 by the end of 2011. From our home base near Washington, DC, we’ve been growing by leaps and bounds, and we’ve recently opened a new office in San Francisco to help us continue to do that.</p>

    <p>In November, 2010, we raised $50 million in a strategic round of financing from Accel Partners and Kleiner Perkins Caufield & Byers, with participation from New Enterprise Associates, our largest investor—three of the best venture capital firms in the business. Their investment will support our rapid expansion and accelerate our product development efforts in 2011. (If you’d like to read the full press release, <a href="http://www.opower.com/Press/OPOWERRaises50MillioninSeriesCFinancing.aspx">it’s here</a>.)</p>

    <p>Meanwhile, we’re doubling the total amount of energy we’re helping North Americans save at home every six months: by the end of 2011, the amount of energy we’ll have saved will be more than a third of the energy produced by entire US solar industry—and we’re having a great time doing it! We’re a company that’s deeply committed to transparency and to our staff, and we were built with collaboration, collective success, and quality of life for all in mind.</p>

